          </dl>
        </dd>

                  <dt>Descriptions</dt>
          <dd>
            <dl>
                              <dt>Description</dt>
                <dd>This remarkable statuette is a small-scale copy of a lost life-size bronze statue that honored the Athenian orator and statesman Demosthenes. It illustrates a trend toward realism in Greek portraiture of the third century BCE and offers a posthumous psychological interpretation of the eloquent but ill-fated champion of Athenian liberty against Macedonian dominance. <br />
<br />
<br />
</dd>
                                                       </dl>
          </dd>
        
